examples.en: Do you mean to threaten?
The mugger threatened him with a gun.
A storm is threatening.
Dark clouds threatened rain.
The city was threatened by the epidemic.
He threatened me when I tried to call the police.
The clouds threaten rain.
Danger threatens.
He threatened to take them to court.
The practice threatens to become general.
Famine threatens the district.
Britain's fishing industry remains threatened.
All we need do is threaten them.
Poaching threatens the survival of the rhino.
These influences threaten the very framework of our society.
Her response to their decision was to threaten to quit her job.
Then he became angry and threatened that he would go to the police.
These problems threaten the very foundations of modern society.
Postal workers are threatening a strike if they don't receive a pay increase.
The latest news threatens trouble for the economy.
Civil war has been threatening the country for years.
Overfishing threatens the survival of certain fish species.
Large areas of the jungle are now threatened with destruction.
The rebels threaten to seize civilian hostages.
Fundamentalists threaten to perturb the social order.
These scandals could threaten the vitality of the sport.
Some of these corporations threaten to sue at the drop of a hat.
Threaten to carve him up if he won't give the money, that should make him do it!
She threatened to quit if they didn't give her a raise, but no one believed her.
Many fishermen believe that the new regulations threaten their livelihoods.
